Type probe Module chaosreliably.activities.slo.probes Name compute_slo Return list <p>Computes the given SLO and return a list of outcomes for each error budget policies in the <code>config</code>.</p> <p>This is a wrapper around https://github.com/google/slo-generator so all of its documentation applies for the definition of the <code>slo</code> and <code>config</code> objects. The former contains the the SLO description while the latter describes where to source SLIs from and the error budget policies.</p> <p>The most notable difference is that we disable any exporters so there is no need to define them in your objects.</p> <p>Signature:</p> <pre><code>def compute_slo(
        slo: Dict[str, Any],
        config: Dict[str, Any],
        configuration: Dict[str, Dict[str, str]] = None,
        secrets: Dict[str, Dict[str, str]] = None) -&gt; List[Dict[str, Any]]:
    pass
</code></pre> <p>Arguments:</p> Name Type Default Required slo mapping Yes config mapping Yes <p>Usage:</p> JSONYAML <pre><code>{
  "name": "compute-slo",
  "type": "probe",
  "provider": {
    "type": "python",
    "module": "chaosreliably.activities.slo.probes",
    "func": "compute_slo",
    "arguments": {
      "slo": {},
      "config": {}
    }
  }
}
</code></pre> <pre><code>name: compute-slo
provider:
  arguments:
    config: {}
    slo: {}
  func: compute_slo
  module: chaosreliably.activities.slo.probes
  type: python
type: probe
</code></pre>

